dt: {bc}a male person {bc}a man or a boy
{bc}an individual of the sex that is typically capable of producing small, usually motile gametes (such as sperm or spermatozoa) which fertilize the eggs of a female

et: Middle English, from Anglo-French {it}masle, male{/it}, adjective & noun, from Latin {it}masculus{/it} {ma}{mat|masculine|}{/ma}
shortdef: a male person : a man or a boy
an individual of the sex that is typically capable of producing small, usually motile gametes (such as sperm or spermatozoa) which fertilize the eggs of a female
a plant having stamens but no pistils
